# HarmonyOS Workspace Structure Rules

## Platform Detection

- This workspace supports both macOS/Linux and Windows.
- Detect platform via `uname -s`:
  - `MINGW*` / `MSYS*` / `CYGWIN*` → Windows
  - `Darwin` / `Linux` → Unix
- Use `.bat` scripts on Windows, `.sh` scripts on Unix.

## Root Rules

- Do not restore `hvigorfile.ts`, `build-profile.json5`, `oh-package.json5`, or other HarmonyOS project files to repository root.
- Keep root limited to documentation, `.r2mo/` material, `.cursor/rules/`, logs, and shared scripts such as `start-simulator.sh` / `start-simulator.bat`.
- Every real app must remain isolated inside its own top-level `app-*` directory.

## App Rules

- Each `app-*` directory is a standalone HarmonyOS app project.
- Each app must own its own `AppScope/`, `entry/`, `build-profile.json5`, `oh-package.json5`, `hvigorfile.ts`, and `app.json`.
- Each app must provide `dev-build.sh`, `dev-start.sh`, `dev-stop.sh`, and `run-start.sh` (Unix) plus matching `.bat` variants (Windows).
- Shared shell logic should stay inside each app’s `scripts/common.sh` (Unix) and `scripts/common.bat` (Windows).

## App Relationship Source Of Truth

Use each app’s `app.json` for:

- `bundleName`
- `moduleName`
- `abilityName`
- `dependsOn`
- `launchTargets`

## Current App Set

- `app-center`: unified launcher and app center
- `app-monitor`: monitoring app
- `app-security`: security app
- `app-hello`: sample business app
- `app-medication`: medication reminder app for elderly health
